<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1608,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[269,406,1608,1632]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs. 27–29</figureCitation>
). Brown, grey pruinose, more distinct in certain angles; trochanter partly yellow. Fore tibia clavate with posterodorsal row of long setae, distal setae longer and placed dorsally, posterior row with distinct shorter setae, distal setae longer; fore tarsomere 1 (
<figureCitation box="[617,696,1680,1704]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly swollen, almost 2X wider than tibia and about 0.7X length of fore tibia, with some setae longer dorsally than ventrally. Mid tibia (
<figureCitation box="[972,1055,1716,1740]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) with long posterodorsal setae, 2 anteroventral, 2 posterodorsal placed submedially, and apical crown of shorter setae. Hind leg (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1259,1752,1776]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) with short subequal dorsal setae; tarsomere 1 with setae longer dorsally than ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1608,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[279,367,1824,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with brown veins. Costal vein with robust seta at base (not illustrated in figure); pterostigma indistinct at apex of costal cell; A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[682,690,1875,1889]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">1</subScript>
evanescent. R 
<quantity box="[856,895,1860,1889]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" unit="in" value="4.0">
<subScript attach="left" box="[856,864,1875,1889]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">4</subScript>
in
</quantity>
left wing slightly disrupted (an anomaly) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[222,230,1914,1928]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">1</subScript>
almost entirely evanescent. Halter brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1608,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
Abdomen brown, distinct grey pruinose in anterior view; all setae clear, but longer laterally than dorsally and uniserial on tergite 7 posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[590,673,1974,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[809,890,1974,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with distinct posterolateral setae. Sternites concolorous with tergites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1084]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[331,455,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 31–34</figureCitation>
). In natural position rather vertical. Cercus and lobe formed by cercal plate + bacilliform sclerite somewhat fused. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[565,645,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with distinct cleft dorsally. Hypandrum (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1239,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Figs. 33–34</figureCitation>
) with two projections more sclerotized distally. Phallus slightly longer than postgonite apex. Postgonite sinuous. Ejaculatory apodeme lamella-form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1084]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Female. Described originally as: setae short, first fore tarsomere not swollen; terminalia with lanceolate apical lamella, black, matte.</paragraph>
