<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1084]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,512,536]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on 
<specimenCount box="[722,897,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
from the same locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1181,1265,511,535]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. The only specimen remaining in Dresden is labelled 
<typeStatus box="[574,677,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">lectotype</typeStatus>
accordingly to fix and stabilize the current concept of the name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1084]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,583,608]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
Unfortunately the postpedicel is missing in the male specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[1121,1255,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1121,1255,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it was not described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[296,445,620,644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" pagination="298 - 407" refId="ref9061" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Fam. Empididae. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, 91, 298 - 407." type="journal article" year="1909">Bezzi (1909)</bibRefCitation>
. If the stylus is very short and basal stout part (= segment 1 of stylus) very little longer than broad, as stated in couplet 21, it runs to couplet 22 of 
<taxonomicName authority="Collin, 1933" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[814,1075,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[814,927,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. tibialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[935,1075,655,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because the first tarsomere 1 of male is 0.75X length of tibia. The other two characters of this couplet do not fit 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[1040,1169,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1040,1169,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hind tibia of male with longer soft hairs beneath (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[559,690,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[559,690,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and halter greyish (yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[1044,1175,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1044,1175,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, couplet 22 also list hind femora as rather stout, concave behind about base, hind tibiae evenly slender and ocellar bristles minute. Based in this combination of characters 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[653,783,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[653,783,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[860,973,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[860,973,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The alternative is to continue in the key to couplet 24 with antennal stylus longer. If so, considering femora without stout bristles or spines below, occipital bristles more than uniserial above, male fore tarsomere 1 dilated, frons with 1–2 pairs of longer bristles mixed with short hairs (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[285,415,909,932]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[285,415,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several pairs of setae subequal in length), thorax grey with four brown bands, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to couplet 38 of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[455,567,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idonea">
<emphasis box="[455,567,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. idonea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species have a posterodorsal protuberance on the epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1431,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
; Collin:134, fig. 25e), but differ in postgonite shape, sinuous and same diameter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[1091,1221,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1091,1221,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and rather straight and enlarged subapically in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[473,585,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idonea">
<emphasis box="[473,585,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. idonea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[670,802,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[670,802,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a short radial fork with section of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1271,1295,1031,1045]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">4+5</subScript>
1.8X longer than section of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[341,349,1070,1084]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">5</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[364,445,1055,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[508,619,1055,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idonea">
<emphasis box="[508,619,1055,1079]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">H. idonea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long fork.
</paragraph>
